{"id":"project-LICHEN-kqj0","title":"SCHC: Potential integer overflow in uncompressed fallback size calculation","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/schc/schc.c
Line: 1505

In lichen_schc_compress(), when falling back to uncompressed passthrough:

```c
size_t needed = 1 + pkt_len;
if (out_len < needed) {
    return SCHC_ERR_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
}
```

If pkt_len is close to SIZE_MAX (theoretically possible on 32-bit systems), the addition could wrap around, causing needed to be smaller than pkt_len. This would pass the bounds check incorrectly, then memcpy would write beyond the buffer.

Impact:
- Buffer overflow on 32-bit systems with malicious/corrupted packet sizes
- Practically unlikely but theoretically exploitable in embedded contexts

Fix: Check for overflow before the addition:
```c
if (pkt_len > SIZE_MAX - 1) {
    return SCHC_ERR_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
}
size_t needed = 1 + pkt_len;
```

Or use safe arithmetic.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:51:27.213958Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:51:27.213988Z"}

